        <num>CHC 1279.2</num>
        <heading>1279.2.  Legislative findings</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1279.2.  Legislative findings
The legislature finds:
1.  It is in the best interest of a foster child who is adoption-eligible to be placed in a permanent adoptive family as soon as practicable.
2.  The state has an interest in decreasing the delays in finalizing adoptions in order to facilitate permanent adoption and family cohesion.</p>
